    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 997.2 Carrera S is a concours-grade example of the final hydraulic-steering 911. Power is delivered by a 3.8L naturally aspirated flat-six featuring Direct Fuel Injection (DFI), producing a robust 385 hp with a linear power band and a 7,500 RPM redline. The 6-speed manual transmission offers crisp, short-throw engagement, paired with a mechanical limited-slip differential for optimal corner-exit traction. The chassis features Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), ensuring exceptional lateral grip and damping control. Meticulously maintained with zero over-rev reports, the undercarriage and engine bay remain in pristine condition. Recent service includes a comprehensive fluid flush and inspection of the four-piston monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors. A pure, analog driving experience for the discerning enthusiast.",
